<paragraph blockId="62.[151,1436,300,780]" pageId="62" pageNumber="259">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,273,413,439]" pageId="62" pageNumber="259">Notes.</emphasis>
W-Mediterranean species very common in the Ibero-Balearic area (
<bibRefCitation author="Yelamos, T." box="[1102,1279,414,440]" pageId="62" pageNumber="259" refId="ref77185" refString="Yelamos, T. (2002) Coleoptera, Histeridae. In: Ramos, M. A. et al. (Eds), Fauna Iberica, vol. 17. Museo nacional de Ciencias naturales, CSIC, Madrid, 411 pp." type="book" year="2002">Yélamos 2002</bibRefCitation>
) and present also in 
<collectingCountry box="[247,327,451,477]" name="France" pageId="62" pageNumber="259">France</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[395,483,451,477]" name="Algeria" pageId="62" pageNumber="259">Algeria</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Mazur, S." box="[503,658,451,477]" pageId="62" pageNumber="259" refId="ref74858" refString="Mazur, S. (2004) Histeridae. In: Lobl, I. &amp; Smetana, A. (Eds), Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera, Volume 2. Hydrophiloidea - Staphylinoidea. Apollo Books, Stenstrup, pp. 68 - 102." type="book" year="2004">Mazur 2004</bibRefCitation>
). Frequently reported from Sardinia in the literature except by 
<bibRefCitation author="Luigioni, P." box="[151,341,489,515]" pageId="62" pageNumber="259" pagination="1 - 1159" refId="ref74293" refString="Luigioni, P. (1929) I Coleotteri d'Italia. Catalogo sinonimico-topografico-bibliografico. Memorie della Pontificia Accademia delle Scienze, I Nuovi Lincei, (2), 13, [4] + 1 - 1159 [+ 1]." type="journal article" year="1929">Luigioni (1929)</bibRefCitation>
, who listed it among the species of doubtful origin or doubtful identification and excluded it from the Italian beetle fauna, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Penati, F. &amp; Vienna, P." box="[581,901,527,553]" pageId="62" pageNumber="259" pagination="75 - 83" refId="ref75260" refString="Penati, F. &amp; Vienna, P. (2002) Fascicolo 46 - Coleoptera Myxophaga, Polyphaga I (Hydrophiloidea, Histeroidea). In: Stoch, F. &amp; Zoia, S. (Eds), Aggiornamenti alla Checklist delle specie della fauna italiana. VII. Contributo. Bollettino della Societa Entomologica Italiana, 134 (1), 75 - 83." type="journal article" year="2002">Penati and Vienna (2002)</bibRefCitation>
, who consider its occurrence in Sicily and Sardinia as doubtful.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="62.[151,1436,300,780]" pageId="62" pageNumber="259">
No Sardinian specimen, however, was found in the examined collections, and it is hard to believe that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Illiger" authorityYear="1807" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Hister" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="62" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grandicollis">
<emphasis box="[1407,1428,603,628]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="259">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[151,293,641,666]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="259">grandicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can have escaped the attention of entomologists given its large size (
<quantity box="[1109,1208,640,666]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="62" pageNumber="259" unit="mm" value="7.5" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="6.0">6–9 mm</quantity>
long). Most likely, the older records (
<bibRefCitation author="Gemminger, M. &amp; Harold, B. de" box="[362,693,678,704]" pageId="62" pageNumber="259" pagination="753 - 978" refId="ref73296" refString="Gemminger, M. &amp; Harold, B. de (1868) Catalogus Coleopterorum hucusque descriptorum synonymicus et systematicus. Tom. III. Histeridae, Phalacridae, Nitidulidae, Trogositidae, Colydidae, Rhysodidae, Cucujidae, Cryptophagidae, Derodontidae, Latrididae, Othnidae, Mycetophagidae, Thorictidae, Dermestidae, Byrrhidae, Georyssidae, Parnidae, Heteroceridae, Lucanidae. E. H. Gummi, Monachii, pp. 753 - 978 + [6]." type="book chapter" year="1868">Gemminger &amp; Harold 1868</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Bargagli, P." box="[705,873,678,704]" pageId="62" pageNumber="259" refId="ref72409" refString="Bargagli, P. (1871) Materiali per la fauna entomologica dell'isola di Sardegna. Coleotteri ordinati da P. Bargagli. Tip. Cenniniana nelle Murate, Firenze, 111 pp." type="book" year="1871">Bargagli 1871</bibRefCitation>
) were based on specimens of the melanic forms of 
<taxonomicName box="[191,478,716,741]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Hister" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="62" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadrimaculatus">
<emphasis box="[191,478,716,741]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="259">Hister quadrimaculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(ff. 
<emphasis box="[546,631,716,741]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="259">pelopis</emphasis>
Marseul and 
<emphasis box="[815,906,716,741]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="259">gagates</emphasis>
Illiger) and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gene" authorityYear="1839" box="[1077,1245,716,742]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Hister" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="62" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pustulosus">
<emphasis box="[1077,1098,716,741]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="259">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1121,1245,716,741]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="259">pustulosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(f. 
<emphasis box="[1302,1435,716,741]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="259">nigripennis</emphasis>
Bickhardt). In conclusion, I consider its occurrence in 
<collectingRegion box="[789,886,754,780]" country="Italy" name="Sardegna" pageId="62" pageNumber="259">Sardinia</collectingRegion>
as highly improbable.
</paragraph>
